  "description": "This is one of the folios of Sri <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guru_Granth_Sahib\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Guru Granth Sahib\">Guru Granth Sahib</a>, it is a visual representation of the text written in the Guru Granth Sahib. The painting represents the Universe, divided into twelve petals of a lotus representing twelve zodiac divisions. Ten of these petals are illustrated with the Ten <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sikh_Gurus\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Sikh Gurus\">Sikh Gurus</a> and the other two are their origin [ <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kashyapa\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Kashyapa\">Kashyapa</a> and his <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solar_dynasty\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Solar dynasty\">Solar dynasty</a> ]. The central circle of the lotus has Sodhi Bhan Singh, the patron, who got this manuscript prepared and he can be see worshipping <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mahakala\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Mahakala\">Mahakala</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mahakali\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Mahakali\">Mahakali</a>.",
